    "faq.privacy.question": "How does securememo.app protect my privacy?",
    "faq.privacy.answer": "securememo.app uses browser-side AES-256 encryption, meaning your memo is encrypted before being sent to our servers. We do not see the plaintext content. Memos are deleted after successful read confirmation or expiration, and we do not require user accounts.",
    "faq.encryption.question": "What encryption does securememo.app use?",
    "faq.encryption.answer": "We use AES-256-GCM encryption with PBKDF2 key derivation. All encryption happens client-side in your browser using the Web Crypto API. The encryption password is generated separately and never stored on our servers.",
    "faq.duration.question": "How long do memos last?",
    "faq.duration.answer": "Memos can be set to expire after 8 hours, 1 day, 2 days, 1 week, or 30 days maximum. After a successful read, the browser confirms deletion with the server. Expired memos are automatically cleaned up every hour.",
    "faq.recovery.question": "Can I recover a deleted memo?",
    "faq.recovery.answer": "No. After successful read confirmation or expiration cleanup, the service does not provide a way to recover memo content.",
    "faq.cost.question": "Is securememo.app free to use?",
    "faq.cost.answer": "Yes, securememo.app is completely free to use. There are no hidden fees, no premium features, and no tracking or advertising.",
    "faq.technology.question": "What technology does securememo.app use?",
    "faq.technology.answer": "securememo.app is built on a Go service for HTTP handling, SQLite database for storage, Web Crypto API for browser-side encryption, and modern HTML/CSS/JavaScript. The source code is open source and available on GitHub.",
